  "markdown": "OpenAI Scholars 2020: Final projects \\| OpenAI\n\nJuly 9, 2020\n\n[Company](https://openai.com/news/company-announcements/)\n\n# OpenAI Scholars 2020: Final projects\n\nOur third class of OpenAI Scholars presented their final projects at virtual Demo Day, showcasing their research results from over the past five months.\n\n![OpenAI Scholars 2020 Final Projects](https://images.ctfassets.net/kftzwdyauwt9/fd1ae4ad-5cad-47bc-1f005d174d9a/bca7104cc9c94f69029a6662be25a81d/openai-scholars-2020-final-projects.jpg?w=3840&q=90&fm=webp)\n\nPhoto: Blake Tucker\n\nLoading…\n\nShare\n\nThese projects investigated problems such as analyzing how GPT‑2 represents grammar, measuring the interpretability of models trained on Coinrun, and predicting epileptic seizures using brain recordings. More information about the next class of Scholars and how to apply will be announced this fall.\n\nThe [OpenAI Scholars⁠](https://openai.com/index/openai-scholars/) program provides stipends and mentorship to individuals from underrepresented groups to study deep learning and open-source a project.\n\nOur Scholars have demonstrated core technical skills across various expert domains and self-motivation—critical competencies for a self-directed program like this one. They each entered the field of machine learning as relative newcomers, and we hope their progress shows how accessible machine learning is.\n\n_Learn more about our_ [_Scholars program_ ⁠](https://openai.com/index/openai-scholars-spring-2020/) _._\n\n## Final projects\n\nLoading...\n\nDiversity is core to AI having a positive effect on the world—it’s necessary to ensure the advanced AI systems in the future are built to [benefit everyone⁠](https://openai.com/charter/).\n\nIf you’re excited to begin your own journey into ML, check out some of our [educational materials⁠](https://openai.com/resources/). More information about the next class of scholars and how to apply will be announced this fall. Stay tuned!\n\n_Huge thanks to Microsoft for providing Azure compute credits to scholars, to our mentors for their time and commitment, and to all the supporters that made this program possible._\n\n- [Culture & Careers](https://openai.com/news/?tags=culture-careers)\n- [2020](https://openai.com/news/?tags=2020)\n\n## Related articles\n\n[View all company articles](https://openai.com/news/company/)\n\n![city](https://images.ctfassets.net/kftzwdyauwt9/5Wm11GSMw6U7lLDKdcyuUY/3180687ca07ba934009f3c2b9219c10c/city.webp?w=3840&q=90&fm=webp)\n\n[Introducing OpenAI London\\\\\n\\\\\nCompanyJun 28, 2023](https://openai.com/index/introducing-openai-london/)\n\n![Person sitting on a couch in front of a red coffee table in a plant-filled room](https://images.ctfassets.net/kftzwdyauwt9/e3357d5a-b177-4b3a-1edf79a7f2dc/ca1f3418cd72b4eb84c9d1a09dfffc7f/stangel-2022-0421.jpg?w=3840&q=90&fm=webp)\n\n[The power of continuous learning\\\\\n\\\\\nCompanyDec 23, 2022](https://openai.com/index/the-power-of-continuous-learning/)\n\n![Person gazing across the room with an optimistic expression](https://images.ctfassets.net/kftzwdyauwt9/21098b49-868d-4515-ca433071d782/838b1914602aaba2e3d935b70d1fa11b/stangel-2022-0795.jpg?w=3840&q=90&fm=webp)\n\n[Discovering the minutiae of backend systems\\\\\n\\\\\nCompanyDec 8, 2022](https://openai.com/index/discovering-the-minutiae-of-backend-systems/)",
